headlines.description: — Devin Booker led a balanced Phoenix attack with 21 points and 11 assists as the Suns beat the Charlotte Hornets 107-96 on Friday night for their fourth win in six games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 21, Suns use balanced scoring and hold off 4th quarter rally to beat Hornets 107-96

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 22 points and nine rebounds in 29 minutes, and the Miami Heat ended a four-game losing streak with a 108-95 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo has 22 points and nine rebounds as Heat end four-game losing streak with win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner had 19 points, Paolo Banchero scored 11 of his 17 points in the third quarter and the Orlando Magic beat short-handed Toronto 113-103 on Friday night, handing the Raptors their season-worst sixth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner scores 19 points, Banchero adds 17 as Magic beat short-handed Raptors 113-103

events.name: LA Clippers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson snagged an inbound pass in the back court with just less than 4 seconds remaining in the third quarter, embarked on a sprinting end-to-end dribble and sank a driving floater just as the horn sounded.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson scores 34, Pelicans top Clippers 112-104 to tighten race for No. 4 seed

events.name: Denver Nuggets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 31 points and the Denver Nuggets beat San Antonio 117-106 on Friday night in a game played in the Texas capital as the Spurs drew a record crowd in their bid to broaden their regional fan base.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 31, Nuggets top Spurs 117-106 in front of record crowd in Texas' capital city

headlines.description: — Keyonte George scored 25 points and Collin Sexton added 21 to lead the Utah Jazz to a 124-122 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Sexton help Jazz edge Hawks 124-122 in Snyder's return to Utah
